    "updated_at": "2017-10-03T15:47:35Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am unfamiliar with resource_quota system but was poking around in the code. IIRC, I ultimately traced it to `grpc_tcp_listener` and my thought was to keep a counter there for current connection and compare it against a maximum. Then, in `on_accept` in tcp_server_windows.c (I think this/similar stuff can be done for posix), close the socket if over the configuration (there is already path for closing if the server is shutting down).\r\n\r\n"
